// ============================================================================
// BODY
// ============================================================================
//
// Module inclusions defining this workspace's scope.
// Each 'use' directive includes a module in the workspace.
//
// Organization:
//   - Core modules first (main application, primary libraries)
//   - Supporting modules second (utilities, tools)
//   - External local modules last (forked dependencies, local overrides)
//
// Extension Point:
// To add a new module to this workspace:
//   1. Ensure the module has a valid go.mod file
//   2. Add 'use ./path/to/module' below
//   3. Run 'go work sync' to update dependencies
//   4. Update METADATA "What This Coordinates" section

use (
	// --- Core Modules ---
	// Primary application and library modules.
	// [./path/to/main-app]     // [Brief purpose]
	// [./path/to/core-lib]     // [Brief purpose]

	// --- Supporting Modules ---
	// Utility and tool modules.
	// [./path/to/tools]        // [Brief purpose]

	// --- Local Overrides ---
	// Local versions of external dependencies (for development/patches).
	// [./local/forked-dep]     // [Why forked - what's different]
)

